​TGV 3rd Global Blockchain Competition, 12th March 2018

Building on 3 years of successful competitions, True Global Ventures is proud to have executed yet another successful one in the heart of Asia's very own Fintech Hub, Singapore.

This competition was initiated by Dusan Stojanovic, Founder and Director of True Global Ventures - in his mission to bridge the gap between blockchain entrepreneurs and investors. 

We were proud to have  120+ investor judges onboard to assess more than 200+ stunning blockchain startups across 5 very exciting verticals of Blockchain Infrastructure, Financial Services, Artificial Intelligence, Entertainment and "Nikola Tesla" Open Category. This was a feat that has never been seen before globally.

We aim to continue replicating this success in the future and continue to help startups in the blockchain space seek funding opportunity, international exposure, growth and recognition. 

Our winners for this competition were awarded cash prizes between USD$5k - USD$15k. We had 5 winners for each respective category and an overall winner for the competition. Many of them went out to clinch corporate partnerships and funding deals to propel them to the next level. ​

12th March 2018
 
08:00 – 08:30 Networking and Registration
 
08:30 – 08:45 Opening Address
*Dušan Stojanović, Director and Founder of True Global Ventures with 9/18 exits and 3 exits in a week in 2012 awarding him “Business Angel of the Year” in 2013
 
08:45 – 09:25 Panel Discussion (Blockchain Infrastructure)
* Laurenz Apiarius, Partner, Blockwall Capital, Berlin
* Lasse Clausen, Partner, 1kx, Berlin
* Chipper Boulas, CEO and Cofounder, Firestartr, New York
* Dirk van Quaquebeke, Managing Partner at BEENEXT, Singapore
 
Moderated by: Petter Sehlin, Partner, True Global Ventures, Stockholm
 
 
09:25 – 10:20 Startup Pitch (Blockchain Infrastructure)
 
Moderated by: Pavel Bains, CEO, Bluzelle, Singapore
 
 
10:20 – 10:50 Networking Refreshments
 
10:50 – 11:30 Panel Discussion (Blockchain Financial Services)
* Ian Love, Founder & CEO of Blockchain Assets, Perth
* Jun Dam, Investor, Meriver Capital, San Francisco
* Altona Widjaja, Head of Fintech and Innovation Group / The Open Vault, OCBC, Singapore
* Roland Schwinn, Executive Director of EUREX, Singapore (Deutsche Börse Group)

Moderated by: Celine Le Cotonnec, Chief Data Officer, AXA, Singapore
 
 
11:30 – 11:55 Startup Pitch (Blockchain Financial Services)
 
Moderated by: Leo Costes, Managing Director, AXA, Singapore
 
 
11:55 - 12:15 Networking Refreshments
 
12:15 – 12:55 Panel Discussion (Blockchain AI)

12:55 – 13:40 Startup Pitch (Blockchain AI)
 
Moderated by: Steve Melhuish, Co-Founder & Vice Chairman at PropertyGuru Group, Partner, True Global Ventures, Singapore
 

13:40 – 14:40 Lunch and Networking
